The paper deals with the impact of channel fading and phase noise on the performance of wireless communication systems, which are topics typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT), communication (cs.COMM), and networking (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on terahertz wireless systems, which are a specific type of wireless communication technology that falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) and systems (cs.SY) sub-categories.
